### Authentication API Tests
### Install REST Client extension in VS Code to use this file

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@email = testuser@example.com
@password = SecurePassword123

### 1. Signup - Create new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Signup - Already exists (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User 2",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Signup - Invalid email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid User",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 4. Signup - Password too short (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Short Pass",
  "email": "short@example.com",
  "password": "123"
}

### 5. Signup - Name too short (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "AB",
  "email": "shortname@example.com",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 6. Login - Valid credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 7. Login - Wrong password (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

### 8. Login - Non-existent email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 9. Get Profile - Without token (should fail with 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile

### 10. Get Profile - With valid token
# First run request #6 (Login) and copy the token from response
# Replace TOKEN below with actual token from login response
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiI2NTk5MWExNTFlMTEyMzQ1Njc4OTBhYmMiLCJlbWFpbCI6InRlc3R1c2VyQGV4YW1wbGUuY29tIiwiaWF0IjoxNzEyNDU2MjUwLCJleHAiOjE3MTMwNjEwNTB9.SAMPLE_TOKEN_HERE

### 11. Get Profile - With invalid token (should fail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### 12. Get Profile - With malformed authorization header
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: InvalidFormat token

### Notes:
### - Replace TOKEN in request #10 with actual JWT from login response
### - Email and password are environment variables, customize as needed
### - All requests are designed for testing different scenarios
### - Use REST Client extension in VS Code for easy testing
